# LogLife Project Context

## Repository Structure

```
loglife/
├── website/          # Next.js marketing site + dashboard (the main app)
├── docs/             # Mintlify documentation site (docs.loglife.co)
├── call_prompts/     # Voice call prompt templates
└── multi-user/       # Multi-user infrastructure
```

## Package Manager

**pnpm** (v10.29.1, declared via `packageManager` in `website/package.json`).

- Always use `pnpm` instead of `npm` or `yarn`.
- Lock file: `website/pnpm-lock.yaml`
- Install: `pnpm install` (run from `website/`)
- Add deps: `pnpm add <pkg>` / `pnpm add -D <pkg>`

## Website Tech Stack

| Layer         | Technology                       |
|---------------|----------------------------------|
| Framework     | Next.js 16 (App Router)          |
| Language      | TypeScript (strict)              |
| Styling       | Tailwind CSS v4                  |
| Auth          | Clerk (`@clerk/nextjs`)          |
| Voice         | Vapi (`@vapi-ai/web`)            |
| Deployment    | Vercel                           |
| Build         | `next build --turbopack`         |
| Dev           | `next dev --turbopack`           |

## Key Conventions

- App directory: `website/app/` (Next.js App Router)
- Path alias: `@/*` maps to `website/*`
- Most pages are client components (`"use client"`)
- Blog posts use server components with `fs` to read markdown from `app/blog/posts/`
- Layout wraps everything in `ClerkProvider`

## Environment Variables (Clerk)

Required for runtime (must be set in Vercel project settings):
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`
- `CLERK_SECRET_KEY`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_IN_URL`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_SIGN_UP_URL`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_IN_URL`
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_AFTER_SIGN_UP_URL`

## Commands (run from `website/`)

```bash
pnpm dev          # Start dev server with Turbopack
pnpm build        # Production build with Turbopack
pnpm start        # Start production server
pnpm lint         # Run ESLint
```
